      "text": "A 54-year-old woman is scheduled for an elective hysterectomy. During the preoperative assessment, the anesthesiologist evaluates her airway using Lemons\u2019 Law, which suggests that certain anatomical features are key predictors of difficult intubation. Which of the following features in a patient would prompt you to anticipate a difficult intubation?",
